McAfee’s Advanced Threat Research Team observed how a new ransomware family named ‘Nemty’ appeared on 20 August 2019. Nemty belongs to another Ransomware-as-a-Service (RaaS) model and we observed how it is being delivered by using:
•	Exploit Kits: RIG Exploit Kit in September 2019
•	Paypal Dummy sites: September 2019
•	RDP attacks: Affiliates using this method in all the campaign
•	Botnet: Distributed through Phorpiex botnet in November 2019
•	Loader: SmokeBot
